From: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qualcomm: ppe: Accept qcom,ipq5332-ppe
 compatible

IPQ5332 uses the same NSS-PPE hardware block as IPQ9574 (PPE
register window at 0x3a000000+0xbef800 layout matches). The
clock/reset tree differs (fewer ports — 2 vs 6, no UBI32, etc.)
but those come from DT, not from the driver.

Add the IPQ5332 compat string to the qcom-ppe match table.

Signed-off-by: Kamil Bienkiewicz <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qualcomm/ppe/ppe.c
@@ -233,6 +233,7 @@ static int qcom_ppe_remove(struct platfo

 static const struct of_device_id qcom_ppe_of_match[] = {
 	{ .compatible = "qcom,ipq9574-ppe" },
+	{ .compatible = "qcom,ipq5332-ppe" },
 	{}
 };
 MODULE_DEVICE_TABLE(of, qcom_ppe_of_match);
